This paper deals with the annotation and analysis of adpositions in Mandarin Chinese, which falls under the domain of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The study also involves the use of machine learning techniques for automatic disambiguation of adpositions, which could be relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for cross-linguistic tasks such as machine translation, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the study involves the analysis of a parallel corpus, which could be relevant to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
